27/05/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi said Wednesday evening (25 May) that he will personally approach conservative leaders in other EU countries and try to persuade them to support Turkey's aspirations to join the Union.
Berlusconi stressed that when Ankara begins accession talks on 3 October, Italy will continue to lead the list of countries that support it.
He described Turkey as proof that democracy can exist in Muslim countries.
(Turkish Daily News - 26/05/05;
TurkishPress.com - 25/05/05)
